## ğŸ“¡ Network Topology

The project simulates a **hybrid LAN**:

### ğŸ”¹ Wireless Section
- **Access Point (AccessPoint0)** â†’ Provides Wi-Fi coverage  
- **PC0** (PC-PT) â†’ Connected wirelessly  
- **Laptop0** (Laptop-PT) â†’ Connected wirelessly  
- **Smartphone2** (Smartphone-PT) â†’ Connected wirelessly  

### ğŸ”¹ Wired Section
- **Switch0** â†’ Central device for wired connections  
- **PC1** (PC-PT) â†’ Connected via Ethernet  
- **Laptop2** (Laptop-PT) â†’ Connected via Ethernet  
- **Laptop3** (Laptop-PT) â†’ Connected via Ethernet  

---

## ğŸŒ Device Interconnection

- The **Access Point** connects to the **Switch**, bridging the **wireless** and **wired** sections of the LAN.  
- All devices, regardless of connection type, belong to the same network and can communicate (e.g., via `ping`).  
- Demonstrates a **real-world office or campus LAN** setup where both Wi-Fi and Ethernet coexist.

